"```sparql\nSELECT (COUNT(?technology) as ?count)\nWHERE {\n  ?technology a :Technology .\n  ?technology :has_GroupTech ?techGroup .\n}\n```\n\nIn the provided SPARQL request, the `SELECT` statement is used to specify what information to retrieve, in this case, it will be the count of technologies belonging to a tech group. The `COUNT` function is then used to count the number of instances of `?technology` that meet the specified conditions. \n\nThe `WHERE` clause is used to specify the pattern that the data must match. The first triple pattern `?technology a :Technology` matches any instance of the `:Technology` class and binds it to the variable `?technology`. The second triple pattern `?technology :has_GroupTech ?techGroup` matches the relationship between the technology and its tech group. \n\nTherefore, this query will count the number of instances of the `:Technology` class that have a relationship with a `:TechGroup`."